[
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 1,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "After the king was settled in his palace and the"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 1,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 1,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "had given him rest from all his enemies around him,"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 2,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "he said to Nathan the prophet, “Here I am, living in a house of cedar, while the ark of God remains in a tent.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 3,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Nathan replied to the king, “Whatever you have in mind, go ahead and do it, for the"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 3,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 3,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "is with you.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 4,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "But that night the word of the"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 4,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 4,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "came to Nathan, saying:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 5,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“Go and tell my servant David, ‘This is what the"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 5,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 5,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "says: Are you the one to build me a house to dwell in?"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 6,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "I have not dwelt in a house from the day I brought the Israelites up out of Egypt to this day. I have been moving from place to place with a tent as my dwelling."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 7,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Wherever I have moved with all the Israelites, did I ever say to any of their rulers whom I commanded to shepherd my people Israel, “Why have you not built me a house of cedar?” ’"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 8,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“Now then, tell my servant David, ‘This is what the"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 8,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 8,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Almighty says: I took you from the pasture, from tending the flock, and appointed you ruler over my people Israel."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 9,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "I have been with you wherever you have gone, and I have cut off all your enemies from before you. Now I will make your name great, like the names of the greatest men on earth."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 10,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "And I will provide a place for my people Israel and will plant them so that they can have a home of their own and no longer be disturbed. Wicked people will not oppress them anymore, as they did at the beginning"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 11,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "and have done ever since the time I appointed leaders over my people Israel. I will also give you rest from all your enemies."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 11,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“ ‘The"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 11,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 4,
    "verseNumber": 11,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "declares to you that the"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 5,
    "verseNumber": 11,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 6,
    "verseNumber": 11,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "himself will establish a house for you:"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 12,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "When your days are over and you rest with your ancestors, I will raise up your offspring to succeed you, your own flesh and blood, and I will establish his kingdom."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 13,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "He is the one who will build a house for my Name, and I will establish the throne of his kingdom forever."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 14,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "I will be his father, and he will be my son. When he does wrong, I will punish him with a rod wielded by men, with floggings inflicted by human hands."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 15,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "But my love will never be taken away from him, as I took it away from Saul, whom I removed from before you."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 16,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Your house and your kingdom will endure forever before me ; your throne will be established forever.’ ”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 17,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Nathan reported to David all the words of this entire revelation."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 18,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Then King David went in and sat before the"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 18,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 18,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", and he said:"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 4,
    "verseNumber": 18,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“Who am I, Sovereign"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 5,
    "verseNumber": 18,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 6,
    "verseNumber": 18,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", and what is my family, that you have brought me this far?"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 19,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "And as if this were not enough in your sight, Sovereign"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 19,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 19,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", you have also spoken about the future of the house of your servant—and this decree, Sovereign"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 4,
    "verseNumber": 19,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 5,
    "verseNumber": 19,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", is for a mere human!"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 20,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“What more can David say to you? For you know your servant, Sovereign"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 20,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 20,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 21,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "For the sake of your word and according to your will, you have done this great thing and made it known to your servant."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 22,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“How great you are, Sovereign"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 22,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 22,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "! There is no one like you, and there is no God but you, as we have heard with our own ears."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 23,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "And who is like your people Israel—the one nation on earth that God went out to redeem as a people for himself, and to make a name for himself, and to perform great and awesome wonders by driving out nations and their gods from before your people, whom you redeemed from Egypt? "
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 24,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "You have established your people Israel as your very own forever, and you,"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 24,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 24,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", have become their God."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 25,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“And now,"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 25,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 25,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "God, keep forever the promise you have made concerning your servant and his house. Do as you promised,"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 26,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "so that your name will be great forever. Then people will say, ‘The"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 26,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 26,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Almighty is God over Israel!’ And the house of your servant David will be established in your sight."
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_start"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 27,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "“"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 27,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 27,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Almighty, God of Israel, you have revealed this to your servant, saying, ‘I will build a house for you.’ So your servant has found courage to pray this prayer to you."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 28,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Sovereign"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 28,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 28,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", you are God! Your covenant is trustworthy, and you have promised these good things to your servant."
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 1,
    "verseNumber": 29,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": "Now be pleased to bless the house of your servant, that it may continue forever in your sight; for you, Sovereign"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 2,
    "verseNumber": 29,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "divine_name_text",
    "value": "Lord"
  },
  {
    "sectionNumber": 3,
    "verseNumber": 29,
    "chapterNumber": null,
    "type": "paragraph_text",
    "value": ", have spoken, and with your blessing the house of your servant will be blessed forever.”"
  },
  {
    "type": "paragraph_end"
  }
]